<HEADLINE> Success Rates of Liver Transplants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
        A list of the nation's liver transplant centers and their survival  
and death rates. 
</P>
<P>
        The first number is the number of patients put on the waiting  
list for a liver transplant between April 1994 and December 1996. The 
second number is the percent who were alive one year later, adjusted 
for the severity of a center's patients' illnesses. 
</P>
<P>
        The third number is the number of patients on the waiting list  
between April 1994 and December 1997. The fourth number is the percent 
who received transplants within one year. The fifth is the percent 
who died while waiting for a transplant. Both numbers are adjusted 
for severity of illness. 
</P>
<P>
        Officials at the Department of Health and Human Services, which  
produced this report, caution that individual numbers may be misleading; 
in a few cases, transplant centers failed to provide all appropriate 
data, for instance. Generally, the more patients, the more reliable 
the data. 

