<HEADLINE> Portugal Awarded Euro 2004 Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AACHEN, Germany (AP) -- Portugal on Tuesday was awarded the 2004  
European soccer championships, beating out Spain and a joint bid 
from Austria and Hungary. 
</P>
<P>
	This will be the first time the quadrennial championships are  
held in Portugal. The 2000 tournament will be played in Belgium and 
The Netherlands. 
</P>
<P>
	The decision, following a secret vote, was announced by Lennart  
Johansson, president of Europe's governing soccer body. The 
Portuguese delegation, including soccer great Eusebio, cheered 
wildly. 
</P>
<P>
	The official motto of the Portuguese bid was `We Love  
Football.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Portugal plans to hold the tournament in eight cities: Lisbon,  
Porto, Aveiro, Braga, Coimbra, Faro/Loule, Guimaraes and Leiria. 
  	   	
</P>
