Raytheon deflated stocks today as traders, already anxious about 
interest rates, found themselves nervous about third-quarter 
earnings reports as well. The Dow Jones industrial average closed 
down 231.12 at 10,417.06. It was the blue chips' biggest point drop 
since May 27, when they fell 235.23 points. Broader stock 
indicators were also lower. The Nasdaq composite index retreated 
from its record high close of 2,915.95 yesterday to end today at 
