	LONDON (AP) -- Jensen, one of the best-known brands in luxury  
British motoring, is set for a rebirth 23 years after Jensen Motors 
Ltd. stopped producing cars because of labor-management strife. But 
unlike its sleek forbear -- the four-seat Interceptor -- the newest 
Jensen will be a sporty two-seater with an aluminum body wrapped 
around a Ford Cobra V-8 engine. 
</P>
<P>
	And by pricing their new S-V8 convertible at about $65,400, the  
owners of the revived Jensen Motors Ltd. hope to attract young 
professionals who need not earn a Hollywood-league salary to afford 
it. 

