<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A slow-moving cold front hovered over the Southeast this morning  
while showers fell along much of the South and Gulf Coast. Mostly 
clear skies prevailed over the rest of the country. 
</P>
<P>
	The cold front in the East was expected to spark a few  
thunderstorms later today across southern and eastern North 
Carolina, South Carolina, Georgia, Florida, and along the Gulf 
Coast. 
</P>
<P>
	Skies were forecast to be mainly sunny along the East Coast  
after light morning showers and snow flurries stretching from 
northern New York to Maine. 
</P>
<P>
	A few showers and possible thunderstorms may be likely across  
the Dakotas, northern Minnesota, and the western Great Lakes by 
evening. Scattered showers also were expected across Washington, 
Montana, and northern Idaho. 
</P>
<P>
	The central and southern Plains, the Midwest, and the western  
Gulf Coast were expected to see mainly sunny skies. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's forecast highs: In the 50s and 60s in the Northeast and  
the Northern Plains; in the 60s in the Pacific Northwest; in the 
50s and 60s in the mid-Atlantic states; and in the 90s and 100s in 
the Southwest. 
</P>
<P>
	The highest temperature Monday in the continental United States  
was 108 degrees in Gila Bend, Ariz. The lowest temperature was 24 
degrees in Alamosa, Colo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
