<HEADLINE> Baird To Buy British Banking Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- The investment firm Robert W. Baird &AMP; Co. is  
paying $39.7 million to acquire Granville PLC, a British investment 
bank. 
</P>
<P>
	Granville, based in London, specializes in following media  
companies, information technology, outsourcing and staffing. It has 
branches in Barcelona, Hamburg and Paris. 
</P>
<P>
	The two companies have worked together on projects before, such  
as investment banking for a common client, the British staffing 
services company Select Appointments. 
</P>
<P>
	Milwaukee-based Baird said the deal, the 90-year-old company's  
first major acquisition, would provide an important foothold in the 
European market. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a very important move strategically to get us  
well-entrenched in the U.K. and Europe,'' said Paul E. Purcell, 
Baird's president and chief operating officer. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal needs to be approved by British regulators. Baird hopes  
to close the purchase by the end of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	No jobs at either firm would be lost as a result of the deal,  
Purcell said. The addition of Granville's 200 workers would give 
Baird a work force of 2,400. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
