<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kroger Consolidates HQs, jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Kroger Co., the nation's largest supermarket  
operator, plans to add 130 jobs at its Cincinnati headquarters 
during the next three years by consolidating some operations and 
creating some new positions. 
</P>
<P>
	Some of the jobs will be moved from other divisional offices  
around the country, including the Portland, Ore., offices of Fred 
Meyer Inc., a 900-store grocery chain that was acquired by Kroger 
in June. 
</P>
<P>
	The consolidation will involve accounting, finance, procurement,  
human resources and legal counsel operations, Kroger spokesman Gary 
Rhodes said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	To accommodate the additional jobs, Kroger plans to spend $6.7  
million remodeling and reconfiguring space in its main office tower 
and a nearby building the company occupies. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
