<HEADLINE> Brit Air Chooses Pratt &AMP; Whitney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST HARTFORD, Conn., (AP) -- British Airways has selected a  
Pratt &AMP; Whitney engine for its new Airbus Industrie A318 aircraft , 
a deal worth more than $300 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The airline selected Pratt's PW6000 engine for the new planes.  
British Airways has a firm order for 12 A318s and an option on 12 
more with deliveries beginning in January 2003 as part of its 
effort to revamp its aging fleet. 
</P>
<P>
	Pratt &AMP; Whitney Engine Services also was selected to provide a  
long-term fleet management program for the engines. 
</P>
<P>
	The first flight on the A318 will be in 2001 with entry into  
service in 2002, said company President Louis R. Chenevert on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The engine was created for 100-passenger aircraft which  
typically make several flights a day with quick turnarounds. It is 
designed to stay in service for up to 12,000 flights. 


</P>
</TEXT>
