</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tumbling bond prices and a weak outlook for  
defense giant Raytheon deflated stocks today as traders, already 
anxious about interest rates, found themselves nervous about 
third-quarter earnings reports as well. The Dow Jones industrial 
average ended down 231.12 at 10,417.06. On the NYSE, losers led 
gainers 2,175-866. The Nasdaq composite index fell 43.50 to 
2,872.45. 

</P>
