<HEADLINE> Price 'Drives' Home Point to Garcia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VIRGINIA WATER, England (AP) -- Nick Price has some advice for  
Spanish golfing prodigy Sergio Garcia: improve your driving game. 
</P>
<P>
	Garcia, the 19-year-old who led Spain to the Dunhill Cup title  
Sunday at St. Andrews, defeated Price 67-70 in a third-round match 
on the Old Course. They could meet again Friday in the 
quarterfinals of the World Match Play championship at Wentworth. 
</P>
<P>
	Price, one of four seeds, along with defending champion Mark  
O'Meara, Ernie Els and Colin Montgomerie, said Garcia will have to 
make some ``refinements'' to win on the narrow fairways used in the 
U.S. Open and U.S. PGA. 
</P>
<P>
	``His (Garcia's) short game right now is about as good as  
anyone's I have ever seen,'' Price said. ``It is something about 
that Spanish blood. None of them (Seve Ballesteros, Jose Maria 
Olazabal and Garcia) drive the ball well, but they all chip and 
putt.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``You have to drive the ball well to win major championships,''  
Price added. ``You saw at Carnoustie (British Open) this year where 
he (Garcia) had a horiffic first round (89) ... so there are 
certain golf courses where he's going to struggle.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In Thursday's pairings: Craig Parry, Australia vs. Paul Lawrie,  
Scotland (winner faces O'Meara); Garcia, Spain vs. Retief Goosen, 
South Africa (winner faces Price); Carlos Franco, Paraguay, vs. 
Padraig Harrington, Ireland (winner faces Els); Jose Maria 
Olazabal, Spain vs. Notah Begay, United States (winner faces 
Montgomerie). 
</P>
<P>
	Montgomerie, who pulled out of the Dunhill Cup with a toothache,  
said he was ``more or less certain to play'' in the World Match 
Play. 
</P>
<P>
	Europe's top-ranked player has a severe inflammation of his  
mouth and is due to have a tooth removed next week. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think I should be all right,'' Montgomerie said Tuesday.  
``It's become the most famous tooth in the world, and I've found 
that when I swing it hurts my chin. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
