<HEADLINE> Hoosiers' Ogunleye To Have Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Defensive end Adewale Ogunleye, who passed  
up the NFL for one more season at Indiana, will have surgery in a 
few weeks for a knee injury that ended his college career. 
</P>
<P>
	The Hoosiers' all-time leader in sacks suffered ligament damage  
in Saturday's victory over Northwestern. Doctors expect a full 
recovery. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-5, 266-pound Ogunleye, a fifth-year senior who had  
been projected as a first-round pick this year, was in Birmingham, 
Ala., on Monday to be examined by the surgeon who will perform the 
operation. 
</P>
<P>
	Ogunleye had one sack and two tackles for losses before the  
injury in the fourth quarter on Saturday. His 34 career sacks are 
fifth-best in Big Ten history, and his 64 tackles for losses are 
sixth-best. 
</P>
<P>
	``Wally had another great game against Northwestern and was  
having, no question, an All-Big Ten season, an All-American season, 
and we're going to miss him,'' Cameron said. ``But he'll continue 
to captain this football team.'' 
  	   	
</P>
