<HEADLINE> Politics 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MANCHESTER, N.H. (AP) -- Republican presidential candidate George  
W. Bush will appear with his challengers in a televised forum on 
Dec. 2, WMUR-TV said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The station said the 90-minute forum, co-sponsored with ABC,  
will be telecast live and rebroadcast that evening by the network 
on ``Nightline.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A spokeswoman for Bush's campaign confirmed the Texas governor's  
attendance, which would be the Republican front-runner's only 
appearance so far this year with his rivals for the GOP 
presidential nomination. 
</P>
<P>
	Bush has declined to appear at an Oct. 28 forum in New Hampshire  
because the date conflicts with a ceremony honoring his wife at 
Southern Methodist University. 
</P>
<P>
	He has accepted invitations to debate in Des Moines, Iowa, on  
Jan. 15, and in Manchester, N.H., on Jan. 26. 
</P>
