<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> CBS Ekes Out Nielsen Victory / TV Ratings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- NBC had the three most popular shows last week  
but CBS, buoyed by its two new legal dramas, managed a narrow 
victory in the Nielsen Media Research ratings. 
</P>
<P>
	With summer's end, viewers are returning to ``ER'' in droves.  
NBC's Thursday night medical drama was the most-watched show by a 
wide margin, with nearly 7 million more viewers than second-place 
``Friends.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Frasier'' came in third place for the week, Nielsen said  
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	For the week, CBS had a 9.1 rating and 15 share. NBC was second  
with a 9.0 rating and 15 share, ABC had an 8.1 rating and 13 share 
and Fox was at 6.1 and 10. 
</P>
<P>
	CBS and NBC seem headed for a particularly heated competition  
this year. They tied for the ratings crown last week and only 
one-tenth of a ratings point separates them for the season so far. 
NBC has a much wider lead among 18-to-49-year-old viewers. 
</P>
<P>
	CBS's new ``Judging Amy'' cracked the Nielsen top 10, the  
network's highest-rated entertainment show after ``Touched By an 
Angel.'' CBS's other new legal drama, ``Family Law,'' finished a 
solid 18th place. 
</P>
<P>
	Two shows with identical 4.9 ratings last week have far  
different outlooks. Fox's ``Harsh Realm,'' produced by Chris 
Carter, was a disappointing fourth in its time slot for its 
premiere. Meanwhile, the WB's ``Roswell'' was extremely promising 
in its debut, finishing as the network's most-watched show after 
``7th Heaven.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The WB had a 3.4 rating and 6 share for the week, UPN had a 2.7  
rating and 4 share and Pax TV had a 0.7 rating and 1 share. 
</P>
<P>
	The ``NBC Nightly News'' won the evening news ratings race with  
a 7.2 rating and 15 share. ABC's ``World News Tonight'' was second 
with a 7.0 rating and 15 share, while the ``CBS Evening News'' had 
a 6.3 rating and 13 share. 
</P>
<P>
	A rating point represents 1,008,000 households, or 1 percent of  
the nation's estimated 100.8 million TV homes. The share is the 
percentage of in-use televisions tuned to a given show. 
</P>
<P>
	For the week of Oct. 4-10, the top 10 shows, their networks and  
ratings were: 
</P>
<P>
	``ER,'' NBC, 19.5; ``Friends,'' NBC, 14.9; ``Frasier,'' NBC,  
14.7; ``NFL Monday Night Football: Buffalo at Miami,'' ABC, 14.0; 
``60 Minutes,'' CBS, 12.9; ``Law and Order,'' NBC 12.5; ``Jesse,'' 
NBC, 12.2; ``Stark Raving Mad,'' NBC, 12.2; ``Touched By an 
Angel,'' CBS, 11.5; ``Judging Amy,'' CBS, 11.4. 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
