<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Tuesday, Oct. 12, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Raytheon Cuts Earnings Projections  
</P>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Mass. (AP) -- Defense giant Raytheon Co. is slashing  
its earnings projections for 1999 and 2000, blaming 
lower-than-expected revenue. The contractor said today it also 
plans to take a $638 million pretax charge for restructuring and 
project problems. The Lexington company estimates its 1999 earnings 
per share will be between $1.40 and $1.50 per share, including the 
charges, or $2.70 to $2.80 per share excluding charges -- well below 
the Wall Street expectations of $3.56 per share. For the year 2000, 
the company estimates earnings per share will be in the range of 
$2.10 to $2.25, compared to estimates of $3.91 per share. Shares of 
Raytheon were halted before news of the earnings warning was 
released. They had not traded today on the New York Stock Exchange. 
On Monday, Class B shares fell 50 cents to $43. 

</P>
<P>
	Weyerhaeuser Earnings Up 115 Pct.  
</P>
<P>
	FEDERAL WAY, Wash. (AP) -- Forest products maker Weyerhaeuser Co.  
said its third-quarter earnings more than doubled thanks to strong 
U.S. demand and the economic recovery in Japan. The company also 
said it planned a reorganization aimed at cutting costs and that 
would affect an undetermined number of employees. Weyerhaeuser 
reported today net earnings of $237 million, or $1.18 per common 
share, compared to $110 million, or 56 cents per common share, for 
the same three-month period of 1998. The results easily surpassed 
analysts' expectations. Net sales for the quarter were $3.12 
billion, up nearly 15 percent from $2.74 billion last year. 
Weyerhaeuser stock was up 1 1/8 at 60 9/16 this afternoon. 

</P>
<P>
	Phelps Dodge Earnings Fall 20 Pct.  
</P>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Phelps Dodge Corp. reported its third-quarter  
earnings fell 20.7 percent as a result of the continuing slump in 
copper prices. The big copper and wire producer said it earned 
$16.1 million, or 28 cents per share, down from $20.3 million, or 
35 cents per share, reported for the same period last year. Phelps 
Dodge surpassed analyst expectations of 21 cents per share. The 
results do not reflect a restructuring charge of $700,000, or 1 
cent per share, for the latest quarter, and a 1998 gain of $8.3 
million, or 14 cents per share, from the completion of the sale of 
Accuride Corp. Phelps Dodge stock was up 2 5/16 at 57 1/2. 

</P>
<P>
	Dow Down 159.25; Nasdaq Down 16.69  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Prices were mostly lower on Wall Street today as  
rising bond yields, presenting a more attractive alternative to 
stocks, drew investors away from equities. Just before 3 p.m. EDT, 
the Dow Jones industrial average was down 159.25 at 10,488.93. 
Broader stock indicators were also lower, with the Nasdaq composite 
index down 16.69 at 2,899.26. The Nasdaq was losing ground after 
having reached a new record close of 2,915.95 yesterday. 

</P>
