<HEADLINE> Ex-Cowboy Kicker To Sign With Bears </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAKE FOREST, Ill. (AP) -- Badly in need of a place-kicker, the  
Chicago Bears on Tuesday came to terms with former Dallas Cowboy 
Chris Boniol. 
</P>
<P>
	The team said it planned to sign Boniol on Wednesday.  
</P>
<P>
	Jeff Jaeger, the Bears' career leader in field goal percentage  
(.759), will be placed on injured reserve or accept an injury 
settlement, the team said in a release. 
</P>
