<HEADLINE> Man Saves Ex-Wife's Home From Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DULUTH, Minn. (AP) -- Jeff Odden could have just let the house  
burn down. 
</P>
<P>
	After all, it used to be his house, but after the divorce it was  
his ex-wife's. 
</P>
<P>
	But when a co-worker spotted the smoke Monday morning, Odden  
rushed to the scene, turned on a garden hose and stopped the fire 
from spreading. 
</P>
<P>
	``My ex-husband -- the hero,'' said Heather Odden, who was at her  
boyfriend's home when the fire broke out. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were just standing there at work and one of the other guys  
said, `Hey, there's smoke coming from over near your old house,' so 
I looked at it and thought, `It's awfully close, it probably is,' 
so I drove over and sure enough,'' Jeff Odden said. 
</P>
<P>
	When firefighters arrived, they found the garage, a van inside,  
and a deck engulfed in flames -- and Odden wetting down the house 
with a garden hose. 
</P>
<P>
	``It very easily could have got the house but it didn't, thank  
goodness,'' Assistant Fire Chief Rich Mattson said. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of the fire is under investigation, he said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
