<HEADLINE> Tim Allen Recovering From Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTEREY, Calif. (AP) -- Actor Tim Allen was recovering from an  
emergency appendectomy that forced him out of a car race at the 
Laguna Seca Raceway. 
</P>
<P>
	Allen, best known as Tim ``the Toolman'' Taylor from the  
television series ``Home Improvement,'' was doing well Monday after 
the surgery Friday night, according to his spokeswoman, Marleah 
Leslie. 
</P>
<P>
	Allen was taken to Community Hospital of the Monterey Peninsula  
after feeling intense stomach pains while sitting in his Mustang at 
the track. 
</P>
<P>
	``Tim was complaining about not feeling well during  
qualifying,'' said his business partner, Steve Saleen. ``He's 
convinced he would have gotten the pole if it wasn't for the 
appendicitis.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Home Improvement'' ended its eight-year run last season.  
  	   	
</P>
