<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stocks closed lower Tuesday, with  
telecommunications shares dragging down Milan's market and the 
French market hurt by the performance of the specialty chemicals 
group Rhodia. 
</P>
<P>
	The Paris CAC-40 index closed down 1.4 percent to 4,658.4 and  
Milan's MIBtel index fell 1.6 percent to 33,195, making them among 
the day's worst performing bourses. 
</P>
<P>
	London's FTSE 100 index of leading blue-chip shares fell 1  
percent, to close at 6,174.8, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index fell 1 
percent to 5,358.46, and Amsterdam's AEX index fell 0.7 percent to 
556.12. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 614 European companies fell 3.53  
points, or 1.1 percent, to close at 309.62. The Dow Jones Euro 
Stoxx Index, which tracks 310 companies in countries that joined 
the single currency, closed down 3.10 points at 324.65. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index fell 33.45 points to 3,756.44,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed down 38.31 points at 3,737.20. 
</P>
<P>
	In Paris, Rhodia closed with a loss of euros 1.45, or 6.8  
percent, at euros 19.93, on expectations of a low price for its 
coming public offer. On Wednesday, the company will set the price 
for parent company Rhone-Poulenc's public offering of a 67.3 
percent stake. 
</P>
<P>
	In Milan, Olivetti lost 7 cents to euros 1.87; Tecnost, which  
owns 52 percent of Telecom Italia, fell 5 cents to euros 1.94; 
Telecom Italia fell 22 cents to euros 8.27; and Telecom Italia 
Mobile fell 12 cents to euros 5.48. 
</P>
<P>
	Traders pointed to concern about the outlook for interest rates,  
adding that even though Olivetti and Tecnost bonds have fixed 
rates, worries that any refinancing move could soon become more 
burdensome helped send their shares lower. 
</P>
<P>
	U.K. telecommunications stocks continued to outperform, with  
TeleWest Communications up 4.25 pence at 238.25 pence, and Energis 
up 31 pence at 1,856 pence. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
